21 Section 3. Section 7-15-4210, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "7-15-4210. Resolution of necessity required to utilize provisions of part. A municipality may not
23 exercise any of the powers authorized by part 43 and this part until after its local governing body has adopted a
24 resolution finding that:
25 (1) one or more blighted areas exist in the municipality by finding that at least three of the factors
26 listed in 7-15-4206(2) apply to the area or a part of the area; and
27 (2) the rehabilitation, redevelopment, or both of an area or areas are necessary in the interest of
28 the public health, safety, morals, or welfare of the residents of the municipality."
